First, look through the Database of Ideas in the members section of the Business Ideas Center and find a topic that interests you.  Get your keywords from the list.
Then find experts in that field that interests you, fully research the field, topic or product, whatever it is [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-Way_to_Profit_From_a_Niche_Business_Idea__4_in_This_Series.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="We've had Enough" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/30039375@N08/3873492941/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 6px;" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2492/3873492941_efe100de12_m.jpg" border="0" alt="We've had Enough" width="240" height="160" /></a><br />
<strong>#4 Way to Profit from your Niche Business Idea:</strong></p>
<p>First, look through the Database of Ideas in the members section of the Business Ideas Center and find a topic that interests you.  Get your keywords from the list.</p>
<p>Then find experts in that field that interests you, fully research the field, topic or product, whatever it is you wish to represent, and interview known and respected experts on tape over the phone.</p>
<p>Take those audio recordings, and combine in with a sort of “how-to-solve a problem theme” and you’ve got a physical product of CDs to sell to the target market.</p>
<p>And it is a well known fact since the initial slew of internet marketing products that came out, audio and physical CD products have a much higher value over a digital downloadable product. I know it myself from experiencing receipt of a physical product and I kinda do put a higher value on the physical audio product versus ebooks and digital downloads.</p>
<p>Don’t you?</p>
<p><small><a title="Attribution License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="../wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="© Photography By CalvinCropley" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/30039375@N08/3873492941/" target="_blank">© Photography By CalvinCropley</a></small></p>
