    <item>
      <title>What I Have Learned About Making Money On The Internet</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/1-home-based-business/learned-making-money-internet/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/1-home-based-business/learned-making-money-internet/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 02 Sep 2009 01:02:38 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[1 Home Based Business]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Making Money On The Internet]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Online Business Ideas]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=533</guid>
      <description>I started thinking about how I got to where I am today and how my online business ideas company is basically all centered around that and I thought it would be fun to share some of my &amp;#8220;what NOT to do&amp;#8221; pieces of advice with you!  I have a few (hundred) that are pretty [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-What_I_Have_Learned_About_Making_Money_On_The_Internet.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I started thinking about how I got to where I am today and how my online business ideas company is basically all centered around that and I thought it would be fun to share some of my &#8220;what NOT to do&#8221; pieces of advice with you!  I have a few (hundred) that are pretty scary but might be helpful to you guys who are starting out with your online business ideas and who are trying not to make costly and sometimes deadly mistakes.  </p>
<p>I learned these from trial and error because I just didn&#8217;t have the knowledge of how to do things and I couldn&#8217;t afford to hire a firm to do this stuff for me.  And to be honest with you, I&#8217;m glad I didn&#8217;t or I never would have learned as much as I did.  But I did spend a lot of money over the years trying new products that turned out to be rotten eggs.  Who knew!  So here goes&#8230;</p>
<p>One time I hired an SEO company called Beranked#1 to get me on the first page of the search results for a keyword phrase I was trying for which was pretty competitive but they told me no problem.  I didn&#8217;t know much about keyword phrases back then or how to find them so I thought that if I hired a company that said they could get me on the first page of Google for my keyword then  why not?  I never made it to the first page of Google for some loophole they had that said you would get on page one but not when.  That cost me 100.00 bucks a month from what I remember.  I canceled that pretty damn fast.</p>
<p>I tried my hand at paying another SEO company to get me on page one.  They too told me I could get ranked for my keyword phrase.  That was 900.00 over 3 months.  STUPID.  You&#8217;d think I would have learned from the first time but no, I thought I would give it a second chance. </p>
<p>If you are thinking of paying someone who claims they can get you to page one of the search engines for your keyword think again&#8230;please!  You&#8217;ll just be throwing your money away.</p>
<p>I can also recall paying an SEO company to submit my online home business to hundreds of websites a month.  I think that was only about 150.00 a year but was worthless.  It did nothing I couldn&#8217;t do myself for next to nothing in cost.  </p>
<p>Something else that I remember doing is not understanding that I needed to find a hungry market BEFORE I went out and invented some cool new product.  I tried to create an Angel Registry thinking it was the coolest thing ever and not one single person was &#8220;Googling&#8221; that or anything like it so it sank to the bottom of the internet ocean.  You must have people searching for what you are selling.  You must know what your keywords are going to be in order to get traffic.  It&#8217;s that simple.</p>
<p>My last what-not-to-do story was not following my instincts.  I was so desperate to make a living online that I was pretty much paying for every $47.00 dollar deal that came my way.  I believed every email I got saying that their product would save me from disaster and I too would own cars and boats like they showed on their website.  Please understand that MLM (multi level marketing) can be very spammy.  Follow your gut and go for something that looks a whole lot more realistic.  Look for a company that tells you UP FRONT what you are going to be doing so you don&#8217;t get taken for a ride.</p>
<p>So my friends, you&#8217;ll make mistakes along the way but rest assured you will learn from them!  Keep plugging away at getting your backlinks from high PR sites, keep posting to your blog for fresh content and keep social marketing.  It will happen!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.businessideascenter.com/1-home-based-business/learned-making-money-internet/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
