      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/home-based-small-business/entrepreneur-ideas-play-strengths/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/home-based-small-business/entrepreneur-ideas-play-strengths/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 25 Aug 2009 14:26:30 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Home Based Small Business]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[entrepreneur ideas]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[Making Money On The Internet]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=59</guid>
      <description>Play to Your Strengths &amp;#8211; You&amp;#8217;ll hear this from many gurus in the field of internet marketing and for the most part I agree with it.  
When my clients become members and start searching through the database of ideas for a product they are interested in promoting as an affiliate, of course they are [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-Entrepreneur_Ideas__Play_to_Your_Strengths.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Play to Your Strengths &#8211; You&#8217;ll hear this from many gurus in the field of internet marketing and for the most part I agree with it.  </p>
<p>When my clients become members and start searching through the database of ideas for a product they are interested in promoting as an affiliate, of course they are going to be drawn to something they are familiar with.  Who wouldn&#8217;t be?</p>
<p>But it&#8217;s okay to go outside of your comfort zone!  In fact, I suggest looking at some of the other interesting topics with lots of keywords that have great traffic and learning about the topic in which you have chosen.  Stretch yourself a little.  Do some research and see if you become interested in what you are researching.  You may surprise yourself.  You may also hit upon a huge hungry market.  </p>
<p>The key is finding what <strong><em>other </em></strong>people want; not necessarily with what you know.  </p>
<p>When you start a work from home business be sure you explore all avenues of what is &#8220;hot&#8221; by looking at the amount of possible keyword phrases in the market.  No one says you have to limit yourself to what you know.  You can certainly become an expert on other topics.</p>
<p>Have fun with your entrepreneur ideas and play to your strengths and weaknesses!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
