      <title>Micro-niche to a #1 Home Based Business</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/1-home-based-business/microniche-1-home-based-business/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/1-home-based-business/microniche-1-home-based-business/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sun, 23 Aug 2009 14:33:11 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[1 Home Based Business]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=476</guid>
      <description>Drilling down to a #1 Home Based Business
As you know I am all about niches and finding keywords that people can use to build their own online home based business in affiliate marketing.  We do this in The Business Ideas Center with niches and micro-niches and you can too.
Micro niches are even more drilled down [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-Micro-niche_to_a_1_Home_Based_Business.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-478" style="margin: 6px;" title="Micro Niche to a #1 Home Based Business" src="http://www.businessideascenter.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/microniche1-300x299.jpg" alt="Micro Niche to a #1 Home Based Business" width="270" height="269" />Drilling down to a #1 Home Based Business</h2>
<p>As you know I am all about niches and finding keywords that people can use to build their own online home based business in affiliate marketing.  We do this in The Business Ideas Center with niches and micro-niches and you can too.</p>
<p>Micro niches are even more drilled down keywords in a market.  For example, lets say your main topic is saxophone.  Then you could drill down the keyword piano to get a niche in that idea such as Tenor Saxophone.  But here is where you can take it a step further and drill down Tenor Saxophones to get How to play the Saxophone.</p>
<p>So your micro niche would most likely have longer keyword phrases and be a bit more specific in what it is.  Your keywords would also have less competition but you want to remember to make sure there is still a decent amount of traffic.</p>
<p>It won&#8217;t do you any good to have low competition if there is no traffic!</p>
<p>So when you begin your search for a niche try to boil it down to the deepest root that you can go still having traffic that would make it worth your while to promote this keyword phrase in your market.</p>
<p>Affiliate marketers have the best internet business when they focus of a keyword phrase they know has been drilled down to find low competition but high traffic.  It can be done!</p>
<p><span style="font-size: x-small;">(photo courtesy of thirtydaychallenge.com)</span></p>
]]></content:encoded>
