    <item>
      <title>#1 Home Based Business Idea</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/1-home-based-business-idea/1-home-based-business-idea/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/1-home-based-business-idea/1-home-based-business-idea/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Fri, 21 Aug 2009 12:45:45 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[1 Home Based Business Idea]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[1 Home Based Business]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=467</guid>
      <description>Did you know that the # 1 Home Based Business in the world is affiliate marketing?  Probably!  But do you know how to go out and successfully start your own affiliate marketing campaign with the right keywords, the right products and the right selling technique?  Maybe not.
(This is what my clients do through The Business [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-1_Home_Based_Business_Idea.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="alignleft size-medium wp-image-468" style="margin: 6px;" title="#1 Home Based Business Idea" src="http://www.businessideascenter.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/j0403669-200x300.jpg" alt="#1 Home Based Business Idea" width="140" height="210" />Did you know that the # <strong>1 Home Based Business</strong> in the world is affiliate marketing?  Probably!  But do you know how to go out and successfully start your own affiliate marketing campaign with the right keywords, the right products and the right selling technique?  Maybe not.</p>
<p>(This is what my clients do through The Business Ideas Center except the first 3 are done for them with the database of ideas/products/keywords.)  However if you were to do this on your own the process would be as follows.  I want to give you a breakdown of what you can expect to be doing when you start your home based business.</p>
<p>1. First you should have an idea of something that interests you that you think you would be good at talking about.  For example if you love playing the violin you may want to focus on this idea to see if there is a viable market.  Pick an idea you like and start seeing if there is a niche for it.</p>
<p>2. You&#8217;ll need to do some major keyword research on your idea to find out what the traffic is like, what the competition is like and what short and long tail keywords are available.  You&#8217;ll want your traffic to be at least 100 searches per day in the top position at Google for your keyword phrase match and with less than 60,000 competing web pages on a broad match.</p>
<p>3. You&#8217;ll then need to find affiliate products online that you are interested in promoting based on your keyword research.  You&#8217;ll be in your micro-niche at this point if you have drilled down far enough into your niche to really get a good product with low keyword competition and decent traffic.  You can use the top affiliate sites or simply search for other micro affiliate programs for your niche.</p>
<p>4. Then you&#8217;ll need to create a domain name and get a hosting plan.  This is easy and I highly recommend Hostgator for your hosting company.  You can get the baby plan and add as many sites to your account as you like this way.</p>
<p>5. Create your site with the best web 2.0 tools which means you need to get a blog!</p>
<p>6. Add your content (posts) to the blog with your affiliate products that you want to promote.  Be sure you add a privacy policy too.</p>
<p>7. Submit your site to the search engines, blog directories, RSS directories and social bookmarking sites.</p>
<p>8. Write content daily in your blog using your keyword phrase and sub keyword phrases.</p>
<p>9. Write articles and submit them to the article directories using your keyword phrase and remember to only put your anchor text in the author bio box.  Bookmark this once you have been approved.</p>
<p>10. Create additional sites through Hubpages, Squidoo and Twitter and start your social marketing campaign.</p>
<p>Now, here is the key&#8230;you want to be sure you write daily in your blog while you are starting out so that the search engines notice you and realize you are adding fresh content to your site.  If you want a # <em>1 Home Based Business</em> to work for you, you&#8217;ll have to do the work daily for it.  But the returns will be fantastic.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
