      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=38</guid>
      <description>I just read an amazing article that talked about social networking and relying on other sites to keep your site alive.  I wanted to give you a portion of that article that talks about hosting your own domain (versus having it free and hosted on a social site.)
&amp;#8220;Finally, there’s the issue with where you’re [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-Should_You_Host_Your_Own_New_Website_Ideas_Site.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://secure.hostgator.com/cgi-bin/affiliates/clickthru.cgi?id=nade0213"> </a><a href="http://secure.hostgator.com/cgi-bin/affiliates/clickthru.cgi?id=nade0213"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-411" style="margin: 4px;" title="Host Gator" src="http://www.businessideascenter.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/hostgator1.gif" alt="Host Gator" width="345" height="84" /></a>I just read an amazing article that talked about social networking and relying on other sites to keep your site alive.  I wanted to give you a portion of that article that talks about hosting your own domain (versus having it free and hosted on a social site.)</p>
<p>&#8220;Finally, there’s the issue with where you’re hosting your content &#8211; that “Buy Now” button or affiliate link.</p>
<p><strong>For the sake of God’s green earth, GET YOUR OWN DOMAIN!</strong></p>
<p>Relying on Squidoo, Hubpages, Facebook, WetPaint, whoever to host your “money page” is internet marketing SUICIDE.</p>
<p>Sites change their terms of service (Squidoo just did recently).  Your page can get banned.  The service might go down. The service might run out of money and die. Some asshat competitor might report you (even when you didn’t do anything wrong) and get your account deleted.  The service might decide to change their design or layout and it might kill your conversions.&#8221;</p>
<p>Now it should come as no surprise that I am a huge proponent of having your own domain because you have all the control over it.  Michelle said it best above.  Get your own domain (I use <a href="http://secure.hostgator.com/cgi-bin/affiliates/clickthru.cgi?id=nade0213" target="_blank">Hostgator Web Hosting&#8217;s</a> Baby Plan) and let your website ideas start flowing.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
