      <title>Find a Niche Market</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/small-business-idea/market-research-online-2/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/small-business-idea/market-research-online-2/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 11 Aug 2009 13:42:33 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Small Business Idea]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[find a niche market]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=408</guid>
      <description>Let&amp;#8217;s first start with what a niche market is!
According to Wikipedia a niche market is the subset of the market on which a specific product is focusing on; Therefore the market niche defines the specific product features aimed at satisfying specific market needs, as well as the price range, production quality and the demographics that [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-Find_a_Niche_Market.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Let&#8217;s first start with what a niche market is!</p>
<p>According to Wikipedia a niche market is the subset of the market on which a specific product is focusing on; Therefore the market niche defines the specific product features aimed at satisfying specific market needs, as well as the price range, production quality and the demographics that is intending to impact.</p>
<p>What that means is the niche is very specific and highly targeted.</p>
<p>Here is my example:  The category is weddings.  Now let&#8217;s find a nich in there.  You could have harpists that play for the ceremony of a wedding.  The harpist is targeted.  You could have a Justice of the Peace in your specific town.  The JP is targeted.  You could have florists who deliver for weddings.  And so on.  It is specific and not so generalized as &#8220;weddings&#8221;.</p>
<p>So when you begin your market research you want to drill down to a niche market so that you can identify your audience and what they are looking for.  It will make it much easier for you to find customers is you know exactly what they are looking for and a niche market takes care of that.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.businessideascenter.com/small-business-idea/market-research-online-2/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
      <enclosure url="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-Find_a_Niche_Market.mp3" length="634028" type="audio/mpeg" />
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How Do You Add New Content To Your Website Idea?</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/ideas-for-business/add-content-website-idea/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/ideas-for-business/add-content-website-idea/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 10 Aug 2009 13:25:12 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Ideas For Business]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=403</guid>
      <description>When you think of adding content to your new website idea what do you come up with?
For me, my business is centered around business ideas, marketing on the web, finding profitable niche markets for others to use and helping them get started with their own site and blog.
My site is built like this:  The [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-How_Do_You_Add_New_Content_To_Your_Website_Idea.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img src="file:///C:/Users/Nade/AppData/Local/Temp/moz-screenshot-1.jpg" alt="" /><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-406" title="google" src="http://www.businessideascenter.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/08/googleone.jpg" alt="googleone" width="150" height="60" />When you think of adding content to your new website idea what do you come up with?</p>
<p>For me, my business is centered around business ideas, marketing on the web, finding profitable niche markets for others to use and helping them get started with their own site and blog.</p>
<p>My site is built like this:  The main pages that you see are through my blog&#8217;s interface on Wordpress and I have a static front page that is the &#8220;home&#8221; page.  Then I have my blog which is where I post my new and fresh content almost every day.  When you first start out with your site you will want to be posting every day so that the search engines notice you!  But what are you going to write about?</p>
<p>Here is the trick &#8211; you need to know what keywords you are going to be targeting for your site and you are going to want to use combinations of those keyword phrases in your post titles and in the body of the post.</p>
<p>For example, lets say I sell engagement and wedding rings.  I know that after doing keyword research that some keyword phrases that people are searching for are, &#8220;platinum diamond engagement rings&#8221;, &#8220;14K gold diamond engagement rings&#8221;, &#8220;men&#8217;s platinum wedding band&#8221;, and &#8220;wedding band sets&#8221;.  So when I go to write a new post I would want to include in the title of the post the keyword phase that is being searched for.</p>
<p>This is where you will be writing new fresh content.  You could write about how to tell the quality of a &#8220;platinum diamond engagement ring, or you could write about the difference between 14k gold diamond engagement rings and 10K gold diamond engagement rings!  Do you see where I am going with this?</p>
<p>Use your keywords to create posts or content for people to read and become interested in what you are saying.  The search engines will love this and you will too!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.businessideascenter.com/ideas-for-business/add-content-website-idea/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>1</slash:comments>
      <enclosure url="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/business-ideas-center/Business_Ideas_Center-How_Do_You_Add_New_Content_To_Your_Website_Idea.mp3" length="936504" type="audio/mpeg" />
    </item>
