    <item>
      <title>Spider for Keywords</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/best-internet-business/spider-keywords/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/best-internet-business/spider-keywords/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 06 Aug 2009 12:57:52 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Best Internet Business]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=398</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[
Most new and honest web owners want to take the correct route and earn top keyword rankings by providing good quality content that web users will actually find helpful and useful. They build links the natural way by offering viral link bait in the form of videos, ebooks, articles, reports&#8230; all branded with backlinks to [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Alerted by the scream, the intrepid photgrapher springs into action" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/7762412@N08/3792735023/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 6px;" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2653/3792735023_7519d634dc_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Alerted by the scream, the intrepid photgrapher springs into action" width="240" height="180" /></a><br />
Most new and honest web owners want to take the correct route and earn top keyword rankings by providing good quality content that web users will actually find helpful and useful. They build links the natural way by offering viral link bait in the form of videos, ebooks, articles, reports&#8230; all branded with backlinks to their sites.</p>
<p>Gradually over time, these links will build up and your keyword rankings will go up in the search engines. People will find your content and bookmark it in all the social bookmark sites like Digg, Facebook, MySpace&#8230; and your rankings will climb even faster.</p>
<p>However, since keyword marketing has become extremely competitive, you do need a little help with achieving those top rankings. Over the years I have tested and used many keyword tools and I have listed some of the best ones below.</p>
<p>Internet Success Spider</p>
<p>One of the first keyword tools I ever used was <a href="http://www.grabthespider.com/" target="_blank">The Internet Success Spider </a>by Neil Shearing which is now free. The Spider is a very simple, yet powerful keyword tool because it shows you the major players in your keyword niche. It slowly works in the background to give you valuable information on your keywords. I realized very quickly, with online marketing (like most things in life) information is what separates the losers from the winners.</p>
<p>So once you have secured the top keywords you want to rank for, use the spider to start getting your site indexed.  Keep building those links too&#8230;that&#8217;s what will get your site to rank for the keywords you choose.</p>
<p><small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="../wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="gumdropgas" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/7762412@N08/3792735023/" target="_blank">gumdropgas</a></small></p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.businessideascenter.com/best-internet-business/spider-keywords/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
