    <item>
      <title>5 Tips on Starting Your Own Business</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/starting-own-business/5-tips-starting-business/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/starting-own-business/5-tips-starting-business/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Thu, 30 Jul 2009 13:50:42 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Starting Your Own Business]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=35</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[I&#8217;ve had a lot of experience in starting small home based businesses so I thought I would take a moment and share my top 5 tips with you if you are just starting out.  I had to learn the hard way on some of these tips so hopefully by sharing them with you, you [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;ve had a lot of experience in starting small home based businesses so I thought I would take a moment and share my top 5 tips with you if you are just starting out.  I had to learn the hard way on some of these tips so hopefully by sharing them with you, you can avoid the pitfalls I fell into!</p>
<p>Tip #1 &#8211; Be Realistic.  It takes some time for a website to be indexed by the search engines and to get the traffic you need to start delivering sales.  You&#8217;ll need to have fresh content on your site for the engines to keep coming back and start ranking you so understand that you will be doing lots of content writing on your site at first.</p>
<p>Tip #2 &#8211; Don&#8217;t expect to be a millionaire in a week.  There are so many sites out there telling you that you can make hundreds of dollars a day.  While that is very possible to do it will not happen in your first week!  It takes a long time to build up to that kind of income without spending it all in advertising to get the traffic you need.</p>
<p><a title="Zeszyt od wszystkiego" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/42191644@N00/3768681630/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 6px;" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3539/3768681630_b34a06072e_t.jpg" border="0" alt="Zeszyt od wszystkiego" width="100" height="70" /></a>Tip #3 &#8211; Have a plan.  Make yourself a basic business plan on what you want to have happen in your company, what you expect your business to look like and what you are selling/promoting.  Be clear with your expectations.</p>
<p>Tip #4 &#8211; Be confident.  Just when things are looking bleak, don&#8217;t completely throw in the towel.  Find a new approach to what you doing and test things.  Testing ways of selling happens every day in every company.  Even the bigs ones.  They are constantly re-inventing themselves and finding out what is profitable and what is not.  You can do the same thing.</p>
<p>Tip #5 &#8211; Get advice.  Network with other small home business owners to see what best practices they are using.  Go to the 30 Day Challenge which is free internet marketing advice to learn ways of making profits.  See what other people are doing.<br />
<small><a title="mac_filko" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/42191644@N00/3768681630/" target="_blank"></a></small>Starting your own business can be the best thing you ever do if you are prepared for it.  Take the time to think things through and get a plan of action.  Write it all down so you can refer back to your plan.</p>
<p><small><a title="Attribution-NoDerivs License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="../wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="mac_filko" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/42191644@N00/3768681630/" target="_blank">mac_filko</a></small></p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.businessideascenter.com/starting-own-business/5-tips-starting-business/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Market Research Online</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/small-business-idea/market-research-online/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/small-business-idea/market-research-online/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Wed, 29 Jul 2009 13:59:52 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Small Business Idea]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[market research online]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=49</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Ever wonder how companies do market research online?  Naturally they do a ton of research to make sure the public is looking for what they want to sell and to see if it&#8217;s a viable market for them to dump money into.  The same goes for small home based businesses but with less money to [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Ever wonder how companies do market research online?  Naturally they do a ton of research to make sure the public is looking for what they want to sell and to see if it&#8217;s a viable market for them to dump money into.  The same goes for small home based businesses but with less money to spend.</p>
<p>So there are a few ways you can do some research online to see what&#8217;s hot.</p>
<ol>
<li>Check out Wordtrackers.com&#8217;s free trial if you have some ideas and what to see if people are looking for them. (I actually don&#8217;t recommend paying for the subscription because there are better products out there for less money.  You can see some basic research with this tool.)</li>
<li>Try Google&#8217;s free tool to get a basic idea if you already know of an idea.</li>
<li>Use Dogpile&#8217;s research tool to see what people are searching for online.</li>
<li>Join an affiliate program to see what products are selling well.</li>
<li>Check out the top selling stuff on Ebay.</li>
<li>Check out the top selling stuff at Amazon.com</li>
</ol>
<p>There are a lot of places you can look to see what people are buying and what trends are hot right now and you can do your own market research online with a little bit of time and energy.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.businessideascenter.com/small-business-idea/market-research-online/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Create Your Home Business Network</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/home-based-small-business/create-home-business-network/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/home-based-small-business/create-home-business-network/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Tue, 28 Jul 2009 14:30:19 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Home Based Small Business]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[home business network]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=44</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[
Just because you work from home doesn&#8217;t mean you are by yourself.  In fact, with web 2.0 you are more connected to people now than if you worked in a high rise building.  Web 2.0 just means social networks.  When the web first came out it was primarily static web pages either giving you some [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a title="Wiring Closet: AFTER" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/47632655@N00/3605000402/" target="_blank"><img class="alignleft" style="border: 0pt none; margin: 6px;" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3395/3605000402_e83831e503_m.jpg" border="0" alt="Wiring Closet: AFTER" width="180" height="240" /></a><br />
Just because you work from home doesn&#8217;t mean you are by yourself.  In fact, with web 2.0 you are more connected to people now than if you worked in a high rise building.  Web 2.0 just means social networks.  When the web first came out it was primarily static web pages either giving you some information about a topic or it was selling something.  Now with web 2.0 comes the socialization of sites.</p>
<p>Think Twitter, Facebook, MySpace, Linkedin, Digg, Stumble Upon, Mixx and hundreds of other sites as well.  These sites have millions of people surfing through their sites and commenting on articles, news and what they are doing in their own lives.  It is all about building networks and relationships.  That&#8217;s something the old web never did.</p>
<p>But here is the thing &#8211; don&#8217;t try to sell your product on web 2.o.  It&#8217;s taboo.  Instead you want to build yourself as an authority figure on your particular topic by offering free advice, commenting on how-to articles and by interacting with others.</p>
<p>You&#8217;ll build your presence online and your potential clients/customers will see you as the guru and go to your site.  That&#8217;s how you work social marketing into your daily marketing plan.  You will be bulding your home business network each and every time you interact socially online.</p>
<p><small><a title="Attribution-ShareAlike License" href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/2.0/" target="_blank"><img src="../wp-content/plugins/photo-dropper/images/cc.png" border="0" alt="Creative Commons License" width="16" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></a> <a href="http://www.photodropper.com/photos/" target="_blank">photo</a> credit: <a title="Cloned Milkmen" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/47632655@N00/3605000402/" target="_blank">Cloned Milkmen</a></small></p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.businessideascenter.com/home-based-small-business/create-home-business-network/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Twitter for Your Small Business Idea</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/small-business-idea/twitter-small-business-idea/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/small-business-idea/twitter-small-business-idea/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Mon, 27 Jul 2009 13:40:18 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Small Business Idea]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=45</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[Everyone on the planet is using Twitter so if you are not, you better jump on the bandwagon and get yourself an account over at twitter.com!
Twitter.com is about creating relationships with anyone and everyone you choose to follow or if they choose to follow you.  It&#8217;s like saying what you are doing right now [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="alignleft size-thumbnail wp-image-372" style="margin: 6px;" title="Start Twitter for your business" src="http://www.businessideascenter.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/07/tweet-150x73.gif" alt="Start Twitter for your business" width="150" height="73" />Everyone on the planet is using Twitter so if you are not, you better jump on the bandwagon and get yourself an account over at twitter.com!</p>
<p>Twitter.com is about creating relationships with anyone and everyone you choose to follow or if they choose to follow you.  It&#8217;s like saying what you are doing right now and people get to see it.  But don&#8217;t try to sell to anyone on twitter.com because that&#8217;s not what it&#8217;s about.</p>
<p>In my opinion, every large and small business should be on twitter because as you know the internet can seem very cold and unloving and twitter.com and all the other social networking sites have allowed the internet to come alive.  Literally!  People are talking to other that interest them.</p>
<p>The chain reaction to twitter.com is pretty cool too.  If you start following someone and another person sees your profile they can start following you and it just builds and builds.   And you want to build your network and of course you can follow groups that you are interested in that happen to be what your small business idea is about!  You can get your word out without selling and without being spammy.  You never want to be spammy.</p>
<p>So go to twitter.com and sign up for an account and start tweeting!</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.businessideascenter.com/small-business-idea/twitter-small-business-idea/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
