    <item>
      <title>What’s Your Idea Of  A Top Home Business?</title>
      <link>http://www.businessideascenter.com/starting-own-business/idea-top-home-business/</link>
      <comments>http://www.businessideascenter.com/starting-own-business/idea-top-home-business/#comments</comments>
      <pubDate>Sun, 26 Jul 2009 14:11:03 +0000</pubDate>
      <dc:creator>Business Ideas Center</dc:creator>
      <category><![CDATA[Starting Your Own Business]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[top home business]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.businessideascenter.com/?p=48</guid>
      <description><![CDATA[My idea of a top home business is anything that is bringing in revenue that MAKES YOU HAPPY!  No sense in doing work that is not what you believe in or what doesn&#8217;t make you happy.  
I can remember the feeling I had when I knew I wanted to be an entrepreneur and [...]]]></description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>My idea of a top home business is anything that is bringing in revenue that MAKES YOU HAPPY!  No sense in doing work that is not what you believe in or what doesn&#8217;t make you happy.  </p>
<p>I can remember the feeling I had when I knew I wanted to be an entrepreneur and of course there were many factors that helped me feel that way.  I wanted to be home with my kids.  That was number 1.  </p>
<p>I also wanted to be able to have a creative voice and working for someone else in a somewhat demeaning industry wasn&#8217;t going to allow me to do that.  I was a travel agent for 18 years and followed the corporate mentality for longer than I would have liked but the money was paying my bills.</p>
<p>So when we made the move for me to stay home it was for my kids but also so that I could start my own business.  </p>
<p>I went to the library and got a few books on how to start a business.  I took classes at Clark University.  I made lists of what I was interested in and what I thought would be cool.  Then I stayed awake for weeks wracking my brain on what I could create that wasn&#8217;t already created and off I went to create it!  Did you get all that?</p>
<p>The problem was I had no idea on what the general public wanted or was looking for so I had no idea who my target market was.  I had no idea if people were even searching online for what I was creating. </p>
<p>So I spent all that time making something no one wanted.  Ice Cream Toppings to be exact.  Not a lot of people are searching online for ice cream toppings!</p>
<p>So it was over time that I learned how to do market research so that I could narrow in on what people wanted.  Why create something no one wants when you have thousands of people looking right online for something they do want!!!!!  </p>
<p>Seems so simple but if what interests you isn&#8217;t being searched for or isn&#8217;t a viable market to sell in you aren&#8217;t going to make any money from it no matter how much you like it.</p>
<p>So my idea of a top home business is something that will sell that you do have an interest in.  And don&#8217;t reinvent the wheel&#8230;find already made products that you can sell as an affiliate to a hungry market.  That&#8217;s what will make you a top home based business.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://www.businessideascenter.com/starting-own-business/idea-top-home-business/feed/</wfw:commentRss>
      <slash:comments>0</slash:comments>
    </item>
